[x] nvim maps JSON-LD nodes to quickfix entries =nvim-qflist-mapping $the node id goes into the entry user_data as the invisible stable address, the locator into filename and lnum as the jump target, and the composed name, status, and due into the display text. the CLI never learns what quickfix is, this ten-line mapping is the plugin job$ !2 +nvim %2026-07-11T17:11 <agenda-jsonld-output #002abe33-96f3-4b35-9fec-d4e89b685a34
[x] Make mutation verbs addressable by a bare id =verbs-by-id $complete, update, and cancel must resolve a raw UUID directly with no fuzzy charter or alias resolution in the path, so a client holding a node id acts on exactly that node. this is the write half of the read, verb, reread loop$ !1 +cli %2026-07-11T18:05 <agenda-id-contract #87a4395a-1dea-4d10-a82c-ae0b2e5d8985
[x] Return verb results as structured branchable data =verb-errors-as-data $already-complete, not-found, and conflict come back as typed results rather than prose on stderr, so an automated loop or agent can respond rather than guess. this is what makes the save-gated automation controlled$ !2 +cli %2026-07-11T18:41 <verbs-by-id #ea929c08-fb94-4319-b3e5-d3a3a242739f
[x] nvim closes the living loop =nvim-living-loop $a keybind on the entry under cursor reads the id from user_data, fires the verb, reruns the query, and rebuilds the quickfix list. refresh is explicit and save-gated and the re-settle keeps the user in place. the same loop a human, an agent, or a future GUI would drive over the same primitives$ !2 +nvim %2026-07-11T18:44 <nvim-qflist-mapping <verbs-by-id #87528306-3e4c-4d94-9ad4-bf81fe6c67dc
